\nreproduced accurately. In contrast to the prevailing understanding that the DO\nvariability showcases bistability in the underlying dynamics, we conclude that\nmulti-scale, monostable excitable dynamics provides a promising alternative\ncandidate to explain the millennial-scale climate variability associated with\nthe DO events.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Mar 2023 17:17:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 May 2023 07:54:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-23"}
